STRONGER TOGETHER rated kindly in mid pack on the rail down the backside, shifted three deep at the half, rallied two wide midway on the far turn, could not maintain position, was pushed out three wide in upper stretch and finished evenly to the wire. SENSING HOLIDAY took this field into the first turn, dictated the pace down the backstretch, was collared outside with three furlongs to go, offered no resistance to the fast charging winner and faltered at the top of the stretch. MISTER MESEEKS was allowed to settle trailing the field on the rail and throughout the back straight, made mild headway passing a tired runner in upper stretch but could not get into contention driving to the wire. ROBITAILLE stalked near the back three wide into the first turn, continued close to the rear down the backside making little progress and could not make up any ground on the far turn.
